essful candidate will specify market requirements for current and future products by working closely with customers, sales, services, support and development.</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Responsibilities:**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Gain understanding of the customer experience of all aspects of the product</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Create and manage prioritized product backlog based on business and customer impact</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Work with the global cross functional teams to define release strategy and content</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Performs in an Agile environment with a demonstrated understanding of when and how to be flexible, and when and how to be firm</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Work closely with Program Management to manage the product release process from definition through delivery and ongoing maintenance</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Own and drive operational and hosting requirements to ensure a smooth SaaS rollout</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Define and manage the beta test and early release programs</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Provide demonstrations and presentations to both internal and external customers</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Balance time to market and quality requirements to decide when the product is ready for release</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>* Effective influence across technical and business teams within Oracle</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>**Experience:**</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Proven 5 years product management experience, preferably in cloud solutions, for enterprise level software applications</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Strong technical background through hands-on experience with software development lifecycle</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Strong problem solving skills and willingness to roll up oneâs sleeves to get the job done</p><p style="height:6px;"></p><p>+ Highly self-motivated to work on tasks independentl